Folks that spend more time hating than creating will always be stuck at that same level.

People who are busy building, will never fling mud on other hustlers.

People who are secure, don‚Äôt mock others.

Stay happy, work hard and wish well for all. Keep building your empire.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
This is the best way to deal with online hate - Just keep working and putting out more work that will blow up.

Lots of criticism is not good for your brand.
A small amount of it is a sign that you‚Äôre doing great.

In most cases, hate is thrown in small amounts.

Drink it up.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
85-90% viewers stay with you and support your work.

10% continue to suffer from their own past (and project it on you)

At most, another 5% joins the ‚Äúcool & woke‚Äù bandwagon of hating on mainstream success.

Shouldn‚Äôt perturb you. Keep doing your work my G.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
In the long term, I‚Äôm building an online bible full of useful self help content. 

Happy to take the burden of that 10% slice of haters that those videos (and other pieces) bring.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
What‚Äôs important to highlight here is this :

YOU decide your self worth.
YOU decide your life‚Äôs narrative.

This is true for content creators. And true for anyone who finds success in any industry.

Know your own worth and nothing will harm you.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Criticism is in most cases an outcome of jealousy.

Online trolls can‚Äôt digest that you are ripping it apart in life . Therefore they hate.

And creators who target you often can‚Äôt digest that they couldn‚Äôt grow as much as you could. 

That‚Äôs just human nature.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Trolls and even other creators often ignored the other work. And highlighted only this aspect of the Hindi page we created.

Very likely that many even knew EXACTLY what we were doing with our ‚Äúpackaging‚Äù game. 

But just wanted to pull us down and fling mud on our image.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
For example, this very series was hated on for supposedly promoting the idea of ‚ÄúHeY BrO sEx Is BeTtER ThAn CaReErs‚Äù

Just a side note, another 2 hugely successful playlists on our channel were :
- Career guidance for Indians
- Detailed start up guidance

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Got us some heavy views. 
Got us lots of subscribers as well.

But everyone‚Äôs only cool till they‚Äôre the underdog. 

Where there‚Äôs growth, there will be criticism and hate (often empty accusations)

Most hate without checking the content packed inside the video..

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
That‚Äôs the nature of social media.

You have to create great looking ‚Äúpackaging‚Äù in order to sell your work.

A lot of great content doesn‚Äôt get discovered for this very reason.

If I could go back in time, I‚Äôd still package those videos in the same way - ‚ÄúLadki kaise pataye‚Äù üòÇ

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Some of the best work I‚Äôve done in my 5 year content creation career is the work that‚Äôs looked down upon the most.

Made detailed communication skills & personality development videos. But titled (and thumbnailed) them with a hook of ‚ÄúImpress girls with these tricks‚Äù

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text: But success always brings with it some trials...

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Of all the pieces we created, the ones I was the most proud of were all the communication skills and social skills videos that we made.

Indian society was in need for this kind of content.

Here‚Äôs that exact playlist : https://t.co/POszmmVpgK

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Now we were one of India‚Äôs only massy, Hindi language self help channels.

Lots of people were doing motivation, fitness, finance, fashion.

Nobody was doing it under one umbrella. Our numbers blew up!

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Suddenly, our YouTube numbers blew up big time. We had a second successful channel (Hindi version of  BeerBiceps)

Guess we became ‚Äúmainstream‚Äù at this point. 

We were no more the ‚ÄòHatke‚Äô (different) creators that only created smart content for urban Indians.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Over the years, we shifted genres. But we were still considered underdogs.

Rarely ever got hate or criticism. All that changed in 2018, when we decided to create Hindi videos.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
When we began creating videos in 2015, we were the ‚Äòunderdog‚Äô fitness channel.

Had a cult fan following and every piece of work was applauded.

But in the long term, it is extremely therapeutic.

Giving up alcohol, weed or any other intoxicant is difficult in the beginning. But eventually becomes joyous.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Over the last 2 years, I became reliant on tea or coffee to keep me going.

Been off any kind of intoxicant for a while now. Wish to cut off these stimulants as well.

No mental exercise that‚Äôs as powerful as denying yourself of sensory pleasures. Need to experience it to get it!

- How to deal with trolling? Toughen up.
- How to deal with stagnation? Write/upload SOMETHING every day.
- How to secure your future? Find co-founders & build revenue streams together.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
In 2020, we have a 80+ member team working across multiple organizations.

Currently working on 2 more YouTube based digital brands (Our Hindi podcast brand and a Hindi language digital version of 'National Geographic')

Also working on building a self-help based app.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
What did I do beyond running my English self-help brand 'BeerBiceps' ?

- In 2017 : Co-founded @MonkEtweets. Talent management & content marketing firm (50+ work force)

- In 2018 : Founded Hindi brand 'Ranveer Allahbadia'

- In 2019 : Created the podcast brand 'The Ranveer Show'

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
These were the 'social media basics'.

But if you wish to SCALE your brand :-
- Delegate furiously.
- TEACH, mentor & retain a great team.
- Network with people from outside social media (for perspective & humility)
- Ask yourself : What beyond these digital numbers?

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Stay consistent with releases

If need be, only select 1 or 2 social media platforms that you play games within.

Depending on the kind of community you wish to build, prioritise amongst :
- YT (loyalty)
- Instagram (brand money)
- LinkedIn/Twitter (professional opportunities)

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
People will STICK with your social media handles when :
- They see FRESH content (either the style or the information or the feeling of it)
- When they see YOU evolving as a person.
- When you still retain some of the ORIGINALITY for which they'd followed you initially.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
The long term throws up its own challenges - Even your most loyal community members can get bored of your content. How to stay relevant? Reinvent.

How?
- Stay updated with the evolution of social media
- Study in the background (to add layers to yourself)
- Change content style https://t.co/0Tc3Dmyuri

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
As you grow through your base strategy of video creation (could be YT, IG Reels or even LinkedIn Video)...

You can further community loyalty through sharing pieces of your personal story. How?
- Vlogs
- Captions that expose your mindset.
- Tweets

Be a good storyteller. https://t.co/jQwl2M6xBM

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
But in the long term, BIG money will come from brands.

Therefore accumulate numbers and create your own niche.

How to get numbers?
- Entertain or Educate or Motivate

- Create videos/pieces that address people's most common questions/thoughts about the niche you've chosen.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
From day 1 :
- Wrote down ALL ideas on paper (content pieces, growth strategies, future targets)
- Decided to expand my team, whenever my income allowed me to.
- Make. Money. First. 
Don't just rely on YouTube income or brands for money. You may also provide SERVICES to fans. https://t.co/JxTnwR5QZ7

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
9. The pressure of not glorifying the mental toughness that you're born with as a man.

Its important to encourage men to cry and vent. Its also important to remind ourselves of the centuries of men who served as symbols of strength.

The real beauty of men lies in ruggedness.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
8. The pressure of not saying something unintentionally inappropriate in public.

...Then eventually, in private, curse the "Dont-worry-babe-men-are-trash" brothers who made public discussions harder for the rest of us. 

...Then eventually continue discussing sport.

SIMPS.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
7. The pressure of speed.

Athletes & hot shot founders have already aced it in their careers. You'll question yourself about your own career's pace right from college.

...Then eventually realize that there's a plan for everyone.  And your hustle is also fulfilling your dreams.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
6. Having unrealistic body image issues set by Bollywood actors.

No matter what you do, you'll always retain that last bit of belly/moob fat.

...Then eventually you'll watch a bunch of YouTube videos on steroid use and feel better about your choices & (lack of) body struggles.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
5. Seeing your body change drastically with time, often in deteriorating ways.

You aren't the fast & athletic brother that you once were. Bit by bit there's a drop in energy as well.

...Then eventually you realize that at least your main body functions are working perfectly üí™

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
4. Having a joke fall flat. Or having your girl call another guy funnier than you.

...Then eventually winning back peoples hearts with your stellar sense of humour.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
3. Letting your teammates down.

Nothing is worse than you failing at your tasks during a game of sports (or a professional task), when the team depends on you.

... Then eventually coming together after the game/job and having a laugh about it.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
2. Often (mainly during a vulnerable childhood and teenage), being told :-

"Why are you crying? Only girls cry."

... Then eventually finding the peace that tears provide, behind closed doors. And releasing years of pent up emotion in a few crying sessions in your 20s.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
1. Facing a lifetime full of pressure from society.

"Son, work hard or you'll amount to nothing"

"If you amount to nothing, you'll be worth nothing in society."

...Then eventually finding your calling in life. And proving the doubters wrong.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
The most beautiful part of this journey is not the viral videos or the money or the adulation.

The most beautiful part is the memories I've created with my teams.

Going to battle together.
Crying together. 
Growing together.

Chase this game. Not the fame. It's not sustainable.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
While kids these days say they wish to become content creators or social media stars, its important for them to know this side of things as well.

Be an entrepreneur.  An entrepreneur that builds teams, brands, videos, content & products.

Achieve fame.
Use fame.
Create wealth.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
So while I've mostly highlighted negatives of this life, let's also highlight a huge positive.

Running a big personal brand will create numerous jobs if you play the game right.

The soaring ups & deflating downs are a constant in this content career.

A team will keep you sane.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
The more you grow, the more the fame will increase. The more you will get isolated. The more you will lose your relevance. The closer you will move towards a downfall.

Currently seeing a few downfalls starting to happen around me

The solution in this case IS TEAM-BUILDING.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
I urge every single creator/potential-creator, to approach this career just as they would a business.

It is not a sustainable career if you're going into it alone.

At some point, you will need help. You will need people to speak to. You will need the right kind of feedback.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
One huge solution for me has been the process of team building.

Of course, as you grow... the weight of expectation increases.

But a team by your side helps you deal with the pressure.

Today, I have a writing unit, editing unit, business development unit & a social media unit.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Most YouTubers & creators fade away because they fail here.

No matter how good your content was at one point, the world demands more from you as you grow.

Mental health issues, career pressure, status games & insecurity are widespread in my world. Audiences just don't see it.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Every content creator MUST reinvent in order to stay relevant.

This is much easier said than done. It includes :
- Studying a lot, behind the scenes.
- Taking tough feedback.
- Not getting carried away into the highs of a good phase (because you know a bad one is coming...)

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
So in 2020, you either :
1. Keep making FRESH, original videos for new teenagers (who were 10 years old in 2015. And are 15 now.)
[- Very difficult because its hard to stay fresh & original 5 years into creating videos.
- Teenagers are very different now.]

Or...
2. You reinvent.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
The only way to survive on YouTube :

Ensure that your content is relevant.

Now imagine that you began YouTube in 2015, when you were 22. 

You grew because of the teenagers who related with your content (15-19 year olds)

In 2020, you're 27. Your audience is at least 20.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Therefore while I'm experiencing peak fame in my career, I'm honestly not sure how long it will last.

As a cricketer, you know that you have a 10-15 year window.

As an leading actor, you know you have at least a 5 year window.

As a YouTuber, you have no reference point.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Because fame and content creation careers are BOTH extremely temporary.

Dilip Kumar is not as relevant as he once was.
Neither is Al Pacino.

That's the truth about fame. Its a temporary high in the journey of a professional.

While you have fame, you MUST MAKE THE MOST OF IT.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Truth be told, the money in this industry is fantastic. 

You make a heap of money even on a single brand deal.

The blessing/curse of my life is that I approach content creation like a business. And all the money I make is primarily reinvested in the business. 

Why?

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
I was lucky. Found the right manager and co-founder in the form of @viraj_sheth.

This allowed me to focus purely on creative tasks like :
- Appearing on screen
- Writing content pieces 
- Content strategy
- Expansion strategy (new channels, new social media handles)

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Along the way, I decided to co-found a talent management company called Monk Entertainment (@MonkEtweets)

Why? Because in 2017, my industry was highly disorganized. And frankly I needed some help with my backend (accounts, brand deals, invoices, events, PR)

Best decision.

Fastest runner, highest jumper.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Because of :
- Indian education system.
- Broken humans who teach for money & not passion.

College Students believe :
- Their field of study is the best & only option for their future.
- College placements will give them their best shots at success
- Marks will determine success

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
3 Life Lessons that I learnt after college :

- Common sense & hard work can teach you any almost job/business
- The best jobs are not listed. They are created when a great skill set meets the requirements of a company.
- Working in start ups will help you evolve/grow very fast.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Marks matter.
They also don't matter.

Students :
Learn to have a dedicated approach towards scoring well.

At this stage of life, your DUTY is studying for exams. Respect your sense of duty.

But at this stage of life, don't let marks decide your happiness.

Detached dedication.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Things you must NEVER DO as a professional :

- React to someone else's anger.
- Disregard the commitments you've made.
- Purposely perform below your ability, out of frustration.
- Compromise on work ethic because of your positive relationship with your seniors.
- Whine.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text: Negative experiences will repeat themselves in your life until you learn what they're trying to teach you.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Whatever you FEAR will eventually find its way to you.

Either in its actual form or in the form of wisdom.

The rule of the universe is to CONSTANTLY remind you that YOU are STRONGER than your fears.

Through experience or through wisdom, your fears eventually become irrelevant.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
In college I was asked :
- Why do you not want to do an MBA next?
- Why do you wish to join the media industry?
- Why do you think you know enough to start businesses?
- Why do you think you will stand out?

5 years on, I thank myself everyday for responding with a :
- Why not?

text: We live in a time where the rich want to become motivators and the motivators want to become rich.

text:
"Always keep a note of the people who don't clap for you when you succeed."

Wrong life advice.

Had read this as a teenager & followed it in the initial stages of my career.

All it did was build up my inner angst.

People are busy. Even your friends are busy. Focus on yourself.

You know how you say you don't have time to meditate or read?

Eliminate "EMPTY SCROLLING" from your life.

"Empty scrolling" is when you aimlessly use social media for stretched time periods. Often involuntarily.

You'll be surprised at how much time you save. Save and reinvest.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
The best communicators are life long observers.

- Observing (and learning from) the communication skills of charismatic people.
- Observing the "energy" & "seriousness levels" of every room they enter.
- Observing the facial reactions of the people they speak to.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Upbringing and content are the 2 most powerful "character shaping tools" in the modern world.

Here lies your answer.

Educate young parents on raising kids right.
Educate young humans through positive storytelling.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Society will be less sexist when :
- Every child attends a co-ed school.
- Every child is given a sex education talk.
- Both men & women are given equal screen time & equal importance in films/shows.
- More podcasts/talk-shows feature platonic conversations between men & women.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text: The greatest joys we experience as adults are outcomes of the greatest pains we experienced in our childhoods.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
A perpetual sense of URGENCY is needed to take the right actions at the right time.

A perpetual sense of indifference is needed to keep the URGENCY from spoiling your mental health.

Calm hunger. Calm execution.

Develop this balance of URGENCY & Indifference, early on.

- BR Chopra's Mahabharat (old TV show)

- Nike ads (Best, BEST storytelling in the world)

- Wildlife videos/articles (Nature contains life lessons)

- Analyzing my most recent work (videos or articles), to see what I did wrong.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Never approach career opportunities with arrogance.

"This should have come my way earlier"

"I'll learn from this and then part ways with the giver of this opportunity"

"This 'small opportunity' is a stepping stone"

Fastest way to stump your career growth. 
People sense vibes.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Many people are gifted with creativity.

But in the modern, demanding, capitalistic world... Creativity is not enough.

To stand out, you must :
- Regularly learn new softwares/tools.
- Have multiple forms of creative expression (writing, videos, etc).
- Work with speed.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
A beautiful life lesson I learnt after a deep conversation with @SadhguruJV :

Don't set long term goals for yourself.

You don't know what opportunities/technologies the future will contain.

Set the same goal everyday : Work with perfection & dedication.

Stay in the present.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Learning constantly is crucial.

Unlearning occasionally is even more crucial.

Many can become intellectual, through learning.
Few can attract peace in their lives, through unlearning.

Release your past demons. Let go of :
- Judgement
- Jealousy
- Greed
- Self doubt
- Gluttony

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
All forms of jealousy arise from a lack of self confidence. 

Either your lack of self confidence or a lack in your parents' self confidence.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Fitness levels are never changed by diets or workout plans.

They are changed by :
- Mentality switches.
- Relearning concepts and unlearning false beliefs about health.
- Practicing discipline.
- Small changes in eating and exercise habits... That eventually compound up.

No judgement = A more secure mind = Lesser anxiety attacks.

text:
My best "character building" childhood experiences :

- Martial arts : Learnt discipline & power of finesse.

- Sports : Learnt humility & fitness.

- Failing in exams & then doing well later : Learnt work ethic.

- Being rejected by my 1st crush : Learnt the mixed nature of life

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Many wish to be entertained, few wish to learn.

Many wish to be high, few wish to derive pleasure from self discipline.

Many wish to be powerful, few wish to serve others first.

Many wish to be successful, only a few actually make it.

Choices are everything. 
Choose well.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Don't let the relentless chase for "wealth" overpower your diet & lifestyle decisions.

Junk & intoxication further fuel the likelihood of stress.

Don't temporarily erase stress through physical pleasure.

Eradicate it through the medium of discipline.

Exercise
Meditate
Fuel up

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Something you understand after quitting multiple VICES :

Physical pleasures fuel the thirst for each other.

Example : A drunk person will also crave junk food.

Conversely, a mind that has overcome one "pleasure obstacle" can quit another one with more ease.

Chase discipline

text:
Not everyone is chasing the same things you are chasing.

Wealth might be equivalent to money for you.
Wealth might be equivalent to peace for them.

You are born for YOUR mission.
They are born for theirs.

Respect everyone's mindset.
Don't be judgemental. It blurs your focus.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
There's 2 kinds of "wasted time"

1. Wasted time that you STEAL.
- When your conscience is telling you to work instead.
- Harmful & incomplete relaxation.

2. Wasted time that you EARN.
- When your conscience enjoys the wastage of time as much as you do.
- Useful & rejuvenating.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Daily habits that I will never stop :
- Fasting for at least 12 hours.
- Breaking my fast with raw food
- Analyzing my task list daily. Even on holidays
- Keeping my phone away an hour before bedtime.
- Meditating daily. If I'm too tired/busy, I will at least pray for 10 minutes

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Realization over the course of my spiritual journey : Aggression is NEVER your own.

A baby is never aggressive. 
Over the course of life, anger enters one's body. 

Sources :

- Childhood traumas
- Influence of friends/family/content
- Excess meat & junk food
- Intoxication

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
'Fasting' has been the biggest lifestyle change I've adopted in my 20s.

Followed Intermittent fasting for the last 3-4 years (fasting for 16 hours; eating for 8)

But a full day water-fast is something that I also find extremely useful once a month.

Resets your body & mind.

If you perceive a road block as a "difficulty", it will become a "difficulty".

Be strong. Not afraid.

Wish health, wealth and happiness for everyone you come across.

Sounds vanilla.

But it's life's greatest hack :

- You become magnetic because people pick up on your positive vibe.
- The universe wishes for you, what you wish for it.

No bad vibes. Only goodness.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
5.

The 5 main heroes represent characteristics of the perfect human :

Yudishthir : Ethics.
Bheem : Mental & physical strength.
Arjuna : Focussed ambition.
Nakul : Charm.
Sahadev : Tolerance.

Their wife Draupadi represents FAITH.

Moral : Perfection is nothing without humility.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
4. 

On the battlefield, Arjuna is concerned about BATTLING his own family. He thinks it's bad karma.

Krishna orders him to attack the more "evil" part of the family with a sense of DUTY.

Moral : Sinning is a sin. But witnessing a sin without taking action is a greater sin.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
3. 

Karna is considered the GREATEST warrior amongst all.

He is known for his nobility.

But he sides with the "evil" clan due to past promises.

He is killed by Arjuna in the war. His side loses.

Moral : Your actions will decide your fate more than your character ever can.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
2.

2 rivals - Arjuna & Duryodhana are asked by Krishna (Avatar of God) to choose between an ARMY or just HIM alone.

Arjuna goes 1st and instantly selects Krishna.

Duryodhana is ecstatic when he gets to choose the army. He eventually loses the war

Moral : Victory is in God.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
1.

The princes are told to shoot the eye of a wooden bird that's placed on a tree.

All the princes describe what they see, before they take their shot. They describe their surroundings.

Only one prince describes JUST the eye. And hits the target. He was Arjuna.

Moral : Focus.

text:

Gaining knowledge is only the first (and easiest) step in the pursuit of success.

The world can take all your knowledge.

It will never take your "quality of execution."

Trust your abilities. 

Share.

text:
Golden College Rule : 

Don't believe ANYTHING a fellow student tells you about the professional world.

"This profession is the best."
"This degree/college is the best."
"You are destroying your career if you do this."

Half baked knowledge.

Take advice only from professionals.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Writing is the most intense & demanding part of my career.

That's the one activity I may never delegate. 

I've discovered that the single best technique to strengthen my writing skills is... Wait for it...

Twitter.

Very powerful & underrated writing training tool.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
What you need to succeed in the media industry :

- People skills (Relationship based industry)

- Genuine love for at least 1 type of media (movies, digital, audio)

- Mentoring from the right people (do internships first)

- A cell phone (This is more important than an office)

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
What I wish I was told in college :

Have the guts to shamelessly say "NO" to the rat race.

Great professional opportunities can be found outside of "college placements"

Choose promising opportunities over safe options.

The world is greater than what your professors tell you.

Creativity is NEVER your own.

It is an outcome of your life's experiences, your genetics, your environment and above all, the universe.

You are simply a channel for the universe to express itself.

Live a clean, focussed life.

Any "brave" human had to convince themselves to be brave when they were afraid.

Bravery is built out of habit and tests.

text:
You are as strong as the words you speak within your own mind.

That's your true character.

If you think weak, you'll become weak.
If you think courageous, you'll do courageous things.

Success is made up of a continuous stream of courageous execution.

Have positive "self talk"

text:

Turn suffering into motivation.

Turn insults into fuel.

Turn losses into learnings.

Turn set backs into checkpoints.

Turn strengths into superpowers.

Turn motivation into execution.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:

- Teens/college students. I understand this. Life will harden you later.

- Aspiring gaming creators. Good energy. Prove me wrong.

- Mid 20s corporate employees.  Along with ganja and daaru, this is your new escape.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Social media is an unpredictable & brutal world.

If you want to survive and make this a long term career, learn to be AGILE.

Learn to be able to change direction and speed as and when the social media world demands it.

To TikTokers,
Don't be disheartened. Be strong.

#TikTok

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
If you're celebrating #PUBG being saved as a personal victory, you're :
- A teenager.
- Not fulfilling your potential in life.

A video game shouldn't be the centre of your world if you're a grown adult.

Life is the true video game.
And others are racing ahead of you, my friend.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
#TikTok banned means :

- TikTok users will discover/use YouTube and other apps.
- Expect YouTube and Instagram to launch their version of TikTok.
- Short form content consumption will still go strong.
- Many aspiring TikTokers will have to stay mentally tough. Move on.

(2/2)

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
#TikTok banned means :

- Vacuum in the Indian market for short form video apps.
- We will see the rise of an Indian social media giant.
- Established influencers will mint money off of the apps who are in competition.
- YouTube has won the "war" to some extent.

(1/2)

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Stiff opinions limit creativity.

Open mindedness and curiosity fuel creativity.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Gossip is fun but harmful. 
It makes you highlight your own shortcomings while you highlight those of others.

Intellectual conversation is hard but crucial.
It makes you expand your mind to meet its requirements.
Only a few work their way to being able to comfortably talk deep.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Everyone is slightly insecure. 

How to lower your insecurity levels :

- Workout for feel good hormones and a strong body/mind.
- Read deep books. Your problems will seem tiny in comparison.
- Practice talking to strangers. Will help you create a realistic world view of yourself

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
The higher your insecurity, the more you will highlight the negative aspects of others.

Those who mostly :
- Bitch
- Criticize
- Demean 

...Are those who are unhappy within themselves.

You should stay away. 
Keep your surroundings positive.
Keep your own energy positive.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
The lesser the evil you speak, the more magnetic you become.

Don't bitch. Not worth it.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
No matter how sharp/witty your potential verbal comeback could be...

If it hurts someone's sentiments, it isn't worth it.

You won't take applause to your grave.
You take your karma to your grave.

And personal attacks, even on your enemies... Counts as bad karma.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Any business eventually becomes a reflection of the humans working within it.

When hiring, look for the human versions of how you view your organisation.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Game changing moments for my own confidence levels :

- When my physique changed due to weight training.

- When I started investing in good shoes/perfumes.

- When I learnt body language in detail.

- When I minimised judging others.

- When I began meditating and smiling more.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Wear good shoes.
Use perfume.
Don't buy too many clothes. Invest in a few that pair well with each other.

Boom. 
You've more or less won the "fashion game"

But PLEASE don't be arrogant/naive enough to believe that clothes and appearances don't matter.

Well dressed = Reliable.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Even "successful" people are prone to making mistakes.

Reasons :
- Surrounded by yes-men/yes-women.
- Overconfidence due to a successful past.
- Not keeping up with the times.
- Delegating to bad human beings.
- Not listening to new strategies pitched by younger folks.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
The combination of warmth and confidence will do more for you than the combination of brains and wealth.

That's why they tell you : "Communication skills are the most important life skill."

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
If I scan my entire career, I notice that there were certain moments which were very crucial for my "networking game".

The most impactful professional relationships were created when I went up to "big" people and began speaking with them, confidently.

Introduce.
Ask.
Build.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Do not fear being judged by others when in social situations. Be confident.

The ones worth impressing are often the least judgemental. Be yourself.

The worst people have earned that title of "worst person" after years of pain.

They need your politeness much more than you need to puke out your anger.

The one that FOCUSSES on your strengths.

Nobody is perfect.

Be self aware.

Stop worrying about the things you can't change.

Worry about the castle that your strengths will allow you to build.

I feel grateful having my evening tea while I soak in the sun

Preserve your positivity!

4. Sleep meets you like a long lost lover.

The average : 
- Look forward to the weekend to chill.
- Perceive learning as "work".
- Get high on weekends.

- Perceive work as a gift and learning as a bonus.
- Learn on weekends.

1. They're too successful/smart to care about me
2. My language skills are weak

1. Everything thinks this way at some point
2. A human with clarity and originality is always interesting

2. Good skin/hair
3. Good smells

...when you're working on your communication skills.

Your vocabulary, pronunciations and voice modulation mean NOTHING if you  look AVERAGE.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Healthy eating begins as battles against your own mind.

It then turns into a habit

It then progressively gets cleaner

Eventually it becomes a lifestyle

Finally, it becomes REWARDING

Stay committed to your body. Your body thanks you eventually. And so does the opposite sex!

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
You may have become rich.
You may have earned respect
You may be chased around for your time.

But never :
- Look down on the service class.
- Stop taking feedback from your team.
- Compromise on time spent with loved ones.
- Lose your child-like enthusiasm/innocence.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
DON'T try pleasing people who have more power than you in life.

There will be many moments where you meet such people.

Either they'll be arrogant and won't be worth your time.
Or they'll be very AWARE of who is sweet talking to them.

Talk to them like HUMANS, not gods.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Procrastination is a disease.
Exercise is the cure.

Exercise requires consistency.
Consistency requires discipline.
Discipline requires enthusiasm.
And enthusiasm is all about attitude.

Have a good attitude towards your "fit lifestyle". And then witness your fitness CHANGE you.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Confidence is not an ability.

It is a process.

You become better at the process when you begin to :-
1. Love yourself.
2. Maintain strong body language.
3. Practice (and be ready to fail at) humour, flirting, sales and deep conversation.
4. Modify until you get better at these.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Wealth is not simply "MONEY". It is these things :-
1. Network.
2. Knowledge.
3. Family time.
4. Relationships.
5. Morals & ethics in life.
6. The comfortable bed you sleep in.
7. Ability to take 2 days off in a week.
8. The privilege of not having to bother about your next meal.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
The only things that trouble you are the things you believe are true.

Does hate affect you? It's because you genuinely feel you aren't good enough.

Do insults affect you? It's because you focus on your insecurities.

Learn to love yourself. Otherwise others will tear you up.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Life may rip you apart.

People will be taken away from you.

Opportunities will be taken away from you.

Rewards that were once yours will be taken away from you.

But as long as you keep working and constantly look for silver linings... A better tomorrow awaits! 

BELIEVE.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
It's said that we attract into our life people who are similar to us - "Your vibe attracts your tribe"

But in truth, you also attract into your life, people who NEED what you are at this moment.

Be careful not to let everyone in. 
You have limited energy. First serve yourself.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Everyone is born with GIFTS.

Life's purpose is NOT to study, earn money and then die.

Life's purpose is to IDENTIFY those gifts. 
Then work on improving those unique gifts called "talents".
Then use the talents to forward your career. 
Then use your career to change the world.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
There will be a day when your dreams will be your reality.

That grass in your lawn.
The cars in your garage.
The home you've built for your family's enjoyment.

But for now...
Work without expectation. True fortunes are created when you're too busy to notice. Stay locked in.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Be selfish when it comes to your time.

Be selfless when it comes to your wealth.

Wealth includes money, power & wisdom.

Don't waste time on people who aren't worth your time.

But in the time you spend working, build as much as you can... To give it away to the deserving.

This will mask their true identity - Flaws, shortcomings, etc.

A true test of character in this case is that person's friend group. Scan their friends' personalities to know theirs.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Stress will never leave you.

But as you age, the definition of stress will change.

It begins as something choking.
It turns into something you're used to.
It becomes something you feed off of.
It ends as something inconsequential... Life goes on.

Don't let stress get to you.

1. Combining ruthless practicality with a boy like charm.
2. Combining a STRONG physique with a deep, multidimensional mind.
3. Combining a fun sense of humour with the ability to empathize with all forms of pain.

Moral : All about the combinations.

text:
Grew up eating, celebrating and enjoying meat all my life.

Meditation made me realize - Every living being has a soul, has emotions and above all - Does not wish to go through a painful death

Going vegetarian has been a physically, mentally and emotionally cleansing experience.

text:

It's crucial to create an education system that encourages you to think outside of the box.

Not just for the sake of careers. 
But for the sake of internal peace.
For the sake of a better world.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
There's always a better pay package out there.
There's always a better spouse out there.
There's always a person more successful than you.

Key to be noted : Go back to when you prayed for the things you have today. Be grateful.

Competition is man-made.
Hard work is nature-made.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
No matter how accomplished the individual - Never put them on a pedestal.

No matter how lowly the individual - Talk to them with respect and compassion.

‚Ä¢ Respect attracts respect.
‚Ä¢ Judgement attracts pain.
‚Ä¢ Bootlicking attracts a lack of opportunity.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
There are pleasures beyond the physical, that most don't know about.

There are ways of life beyond the one we know, that most don't dare to know.

Never judge :
- Monks
- Spiritual people
- Yogis

They never judge you for :
- Your money lust
- Your habits.
- Your mindset.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Skills of a LEADER :

- Controlling your anger : Respect attracts respect.

- Encouragement : Everyone's different. Learn them first.

- Empathy for weakness : Not everyone can match your pace.

- Ruthlessness : Cut off the ones who don't perform. You owe it to the ones who do.

- Be well prepared for EVERYTHING.
- Do research on people before meeting them.
- Back up ideas/thoughts with stats.
- Push yourself to think out of the box and have the guts to express yourself.
- Work harder than the competition.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Whatever career you choose for yourself :

Make sure you're the candidate with the X-factor.

You should be the one :
- Doing things differently.
- Knowing more about worldwide trends.
- With the ability to communicate complex ideas easily.
- Who is memorable.

text:

Lukewarm will just not do the trick.

Life works the same way. The pain you go through is like the super hot water. 

Karmic cleansing is the shower.

Go through pain, to level up.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Things that destroy you, OR make you grow FASTER :-
1. Academic & professional failures
2. Break ups
3. Getting fired
4. Being cut off by people
5. Insults from society
6. Embarassing moments in social situations
7. Making a fool of yourself at the office
8. Admitting mistakes

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Be glad that people, opportunities and rewards were stripped away from you.

"Losing them" was your life's BIG TUITION.

Whether you like it or not, you get what you deserve. The greatest life lessons are painful.

Read this again and again until you make peace with your karma.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Your analytical powers are cool.
Your deep thinking is cool.
Your endearing personality is cool.
Your energy is cool.
Your story is cool.

But nobody will give a shit IF you don't EXECUTE on what you say. Turn thoughts into things. 

Or else, you will always remain mediocre!

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:

It's not a reflection of your worth, it's a reflection of their ego

People perceive themselves to be more important than they really are. 
Or they're just really busy. Chill

‚Ä¢ 1 person is a slave to the other.
‚Ä¢ 1 person's favourite activities are an effort for the other person.

Lived in Mumbai forever. Don't remember a single day where I didn't hear :-
- Construction
- Drilling
- Hammering
- Explosions
- Crashes

text:
LUST for :
- Sex
- Food
- Weed
- Alcohol
- Money
- Attention
- Fame
- And even friendship.
...is not how life should be lived.

Definition of LUST : "I will only be happy if i have THAT." 

Learn to be content with what you have. Be happy, NOW. Focus on what's in your hand.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
You cannot justify eating restaurant food every day.

- Your blog is not an excuse.
- Your peers are not an excuse.
- Your lust for food (Heyy I'm a foodie) is not an excuse.

Your joints, organs, skin and mindset need to be rescued. Start today - Delete those food delivery apps.

An unfit human is a lazy human.

Have opinions, but don't make your opinions your identity.

Give your mental energy to your process of self growth, not to external happenings which are largely outside of your control.

text:

- Swami Yukteshwar Giri

Meaning : See everything for WHAT it is, not through the lens of your love-fuelled eyes. 

Application : Remember this quote if you're trying to get over a person/situation.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Focus on medium term goals
Not long term goals.

You'll never know what the world is going to look like in 2030. But you have an idea of what it will look like in 2021.

Work towards an achievable dream using the greatest weapon known to man - Realistic deadlines.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Life's purpose is what you wish for it to be.

Saying "Life is meaningless" is but an excuse for a mind filled with laziness, lethargy and toxins derived from the wrong habits.

Your thoughts are a reflection of your habits.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Pity the humans whose opinions are a cause for their own discomfort.

If someone doesn't completely agree with you, ALLOW them to disagree. 

A rigid mind is the root cause for all suffering. 

A mind that is open to others' perspectives is a mind that's built for GROWTH.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
My ideal weekend :
1. Completely switching off from work for at least 75% of the time.
2. Getting 1 intense workout and 1 intense football game in.
3. Spending time with family.
4. 1 great Sunday meal.
5. A total of 3-5 hours of meditation over 2 days.
6. Some PlayStation time.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
You will never grow on social media if :
1. You are affected by trolls.
2. Your content is centred around criticizing others' content.
3. You are unidimensional.
4. You are not open to creating video content.
5. You put out more negativity/complaints than positivity/solutions.

- Hated on India
- Glorified the American Life
- Were convinced that India doesn't have a future
- Always put their own financial interests over their sense of patriotism.

... And many of them are coming back now!

1. Relying on TV channels & newspapers for news.
2. Joining in on political debates, communal tension & any form of hate in social situations.
3. Forcing their kids into selecting traditional careers (Btech, MBBS)

There are 2 kinds of successful people.

1. The kind that constantly compares themselves to people "more successful" than themselves.

2. The kind that knows that there is no such thing as "more successful" or "less successful"
... And keeps working towards leveling up in life.

Your friends and co-workers in your 20s will decide the difficulty or the ease of your 30s.

Work hard, learn furiously together and keep encouraging each other. It's the easiest way to secure your future.

1. Accepts you for exactly who you are.
2. Corrects you where you fail to correct yourself.
3. Encourages you to achieve your goals, FASTER.
4. You feel like doing "uncomfortable" things for. If he/she is worth it, no ask will be too much.

100% True.

But you must first LEARN how to make money and multiply it.

LEARNING MONEY MANAGEMENT is a crucial aspect of "Chasing excellence."

Value every coin, save most of it and keep reinvesting to bring in more.

- Apps help you calm down. Not meditate.
- Meditation is about uninterrupted OBSERVATION
- You won't be able to observe with your mind being fed external data

1. Mental rejection of heavy foods that in turn led to much better physical & mental health (no meat & processed food)

2. Best sleep ever

3. Better control on emotions and actions (less anger & sadness)

4. Better immunity

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:

Science has gifted us the world of MEDICINE.

Science is yet to discover the world of INNER MEDICINE that Yoga & Ayurveda speak of.

Above all, think (& feel) positive

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
1 day of poor dieting isn't going to make you UNFIT.

1 day of clean eating is not going to make you fit.

Enjoy the GRIND without expectation.
Do your best to eat clean every day.

One day you'll look at yourself in the mirror and you would have already achieved your goals.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
The WORST moments of life are often the ones that best shape your destiny.

1. Scan your own life.
2. Spot the worst phases in your scan.
3. Notice that these were always followed by GOOD phases.
4. If you didn't encounter a good phase, you DID encounter CHARACTER BUILDING.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
The human body DEMANDS that you eat clean, exercise regularly & meditate daily.

These 3 activities should be as normal as breathing is for you. If they aren't, work towards making them THAT MUCH a part of your lifestyle

NORMALIZE them. But never OBSESS over them

Balance is key

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Unless you are a FITNESS PROFESSIONAL, never put fitness at the center of your universe.

Modern careers require you to PRIORITIZE your life. 

Unless it is making you rich, famous or successful, don't obsess over it.

Being fit is important. Being balanced is MORE important.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Favourite movie quote of all time, courtesy Batman Begins.

"It is not who you are underneath. It is what you do that defines you."

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
A career without targets is an incomplete one.

Never put unnecessary pressure on yourself. But keep a vision of your long term goal in your mind, ALWAYS.

A horse that knows where to run, RUNS FASTER.

Weekly & yearly targets will be that FINISH LINE for you.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
There's too much to be grateful for.

Pull yourself out of that imaginary battle you are putting your heart through.

Every day is a new opportunity to write a new chapter.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Coming from a life long non vegetarian, who has been vegetarian for longer than a year now.

And doesn't intend on going back üòâ

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
The next time you're guilting someone into feeling bad about eating meat, remember this :-

"What comes out of the heart is far more important than what goes into the belly." ~ Vedic Proverb

Nobody EATS with the intention of hurting. 

You enjoy what you are brought up to enjoy.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
A wise man once said, "The key to INDIAN happiness is as follows :-

Do business with a Gujju.
Eat with a Punju.
Analyze problems with a Mallu.
Talk esoteric with a Bong.
Party with a Parsi.
But love yourself completely first."

I may or may not be the wise man.

He may transform the world

And be honored in history and lore.

But his only satisfaction will always have been

In the secluded, blissful days of exploration

When the world knew not his name.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Things that decide our material success (reputation) :-
1. Hours at the office.
2. People skills
3. Financial smarts
4. Branding/marketing ability
5. Being far sighted

Things that decide our spiritual success (peace) :-
1. Good health
2. A fulfilling job
3. Family
4. Karma

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Sadness creates great artists.
Struggle creates great teachers.
Penance creates great humans.

Don't like your job? Resign & then give life your best shot.

Don't like your body? Take that first step & stay consistent with the process.

Don't like where you are in life? Sacrifice

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Biggest spiritual learning this year :

Only react/talk to people after knowing this : 
- Everyone you meet is a reflection of yourself. 
- They are the SAME soul, but they've had DIFFERENT life experiences. 
- Circumstances create the individual.
- Internal respect creates peace

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Maturity is the ability to :-
1. Acknowledge your mistakes

2. Take blame/insults for long term PEACE. 

3. Understand that every human goes through their own circumstances.

4. Not aggressively react to verbal aggression.

5. Understand this :
Peace > Winning debates.

text:
How to fix your heart after a break up :
1. Accept ALL the emotions. Every day will be different, feel all of it completely.

2. If possible, for some time delete them ENTIRELY from your social media. 

3. Engage in a SELF-GROWTH phase - exercise, read, meditate.

4. Give it time

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Aspects of bad parenting :-

1. Saying yes to every request of your child - Leads to arrogance.

2. Voicing own frustrations in front of the family - Leads to a "whiner" mindset.

3. Glorifying an i-Pad instead of glorifying a football - Goodbye physical & mental fitness.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Seen the wrong romantic relationships ruin the best of minds.

Always be conscious of what effect your partner is having on :
- Your growth
- Your mood
- Your other relationships
- Your career

Love has led to the downfall of MANY before you. Don't join that club so easily.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
FEEDBACK LOOPS - Life's greatest "success decider"

The day you block out feedback loops for your career, relationship, behaviour or thoughts... 
You WILL stop growing.

Always stay hungry for honest (some times hard-hitting) feedback from those closest to you.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Your career does NOT begin at age 22.

It begins at age 4. 
When :-
1. Your parents correct your bad behaviour (ethics)
2. You lose sports matches based on pure skill (humility)
3. You are able to co-ordinate with your childhood friends for a tiny play-time victory (teamwork)

The greatest rewards in life are not money or fame.

They are people.

Power through a difficult phase of your life and you usually come out gaining a fellow soldier.

This soldier will make your battles easier.

And very likely will eventually become a knight in your kingdom.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
BEING CALM in every situation is the MOST beautiful high you will experience.

How to reach that state of existence?
- Stabilize physical energy by exercising regularly
- Stabilize mental energy by working at building your career
- Stabilize spiritual energy by meditating daily

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Yogic practices which are EXTREMELY relevant in the modern day :

- Conscious eating : Focus on food for best possible digestion.

- Pranayam : Better skin, hair health; More energy!

- Meditation : Better focus levels & brain-power.

- Vegetarianism : Watch Game Changers üòâ

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Conscious Eating is the practice of ONLY eating while you're eating.

No TV, no conversations, no distractions. Only you & your food.

Enjoy every bite & make EATING a meditative process.

Benefits :
- No Overeating
- Better digestion
- Less fat deposited in the long term

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Places you must not initiate conversation :
1. Gym - Stay focussed. The gym is more important for your mentality than it is for your body.

2. Dining Table - Conscious eating WILL change your life (and especially your fitness game) if you get into it 

3. Urinals - Why bro?

text: "Damn nature, you scary!" https://t.co/nIudQjPvan

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
2 kinds of OLDER professionals:

1. The guru : Humble; always spreading knowledge; always learning.

2. The boss : Arrogant (mainly about their age); always forcing their beliefs on others; not ready to learn from younger folks.

Easy to guess which one is more successful.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Your social media feeds are a reflection of your internal world.

You only follow them if :-
1. You know them personally.
2. You see yourself in them.
3. You aspire to be like them in some aspect.

Social media isn't toxic or demotivating. Your current mindset (or peers) maybe!

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Shout-out to all the kids with a bad handwriting.

Your handwriting (and in many cases, your grades) never got better despite your best effort.

May have been a curse back then. 
But situations like this teach you TOUGHNESS in life. 
School isn't fair. 
But life is the same!

text:

That turned out to be true.
But you learn from your mistakes.

In the game of life, KARMA is currency. Not paper & coins.

Learn to protect yourself early. 
But keep being you.

On the other, you witness people taking advantage of your niceness.

Moral of the story : 
Ethics are far more powerful than career gains in the long term.
Continue staying humble.

- Balance material wealth with KNOWLEDGE, FAMILY LIFE, SPIRITUAL GROWTH.

- True success is heavy amounts of BALANCE, not heavy amounts of money.

Building something UNIQUE
Levelling up your product at all stages

3. Don't keep your vice at home.

Common personal finance mistakes :
1. SHOPPING out of your means : you don't need that overpriced shirt or perfume

2. Buying a car too early : Do you really need a money draining box in the age of Ubers?

3. Lack of education : Aur bolo 'Kal seekhunga"

The earlier the better!

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
3 Money management basics for AMATEURS :-

1. EDUCATE YOURSELF about money. Just learn the ABCs.
2. Focus on BRINGING more money into your account. Dont focus on finance if you can't understand it.
3. Contact wealth managers or PMS firms or FINTECH companies who'll invest for you

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Personal finance basics for peeps in their 20s

1. Aim to save 30-50% of income. Adjust lifestyle to meet goals
2. Cut off friends who drain off money on weekends
3. Divide savings between multiple investment options
4. Get a GREAT, TRUSTWORTHY C.A. 
5. Talk to SMART, OLDER peeps

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Personal finance is the MOST important practical life skill that you aren't taught in school or college

And I rarely see mid-20-something Indians who CARE about managing their money

Live it large guys. But ensure you take ACTION today, in order to live it large TOMORROW as well

text:
If meditation can physically change the structure of your brain, then what stops you from believing that it will change your food habits as well?

Food habits are important for your mindset

Your body starts rejecting a number of "modern" foods after you make meditation a habit!

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
As I'm growing up (and as I'm meditating more), I can feel my body rejecting certain kinds of foods :-
1. Began with meat - slowly gave up all kinds. I'm a vegetarian now!
2. Processed foods - no sugar, nothing that comes out of a packet.
3. Greasy, starchy restaurant food.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Most Indians at 22 don't really have an idea of what they want to do. So you end up doing what everyone's doing.

Before you know it - you'll be 25 and stuck in a career you don't enjoy.

The key to avoiding this situation is INTERNSHIPS and LEARNING NEW SKILLS while in college.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
At 22, the biggest SKILL that you need is CLARITY. 

Not technical skills, not communication skills.

First list out your weaknesses, then list out all the possible career paths that require those skills - Those career paths should NOT be in your plans.

#SundayThoughts

text:
The real benefit of engineering college isn't the technical skills you learn.

The real benefit is interacting with other lazy, jugadoo mathematical minds.

Your friend circle will collectively get itself out of many tough situations. Those experiences are your biggest learnings!

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
"JUGAAD" is engineering's biggest teaching to it's graduates.

I guarantee you - not a single Mumbai University engineer deserves to be called an engineer based on his engineering skill set.

But if you place an MU engineer in ANY tough situation - he'll find his way out of it ü§ò

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
It's been 3.5 years since engineering college. 

And ONLY in the last 6 months have I begun to value my degree.

Why? Because we began aggressively hiring for our companies.

That taught me 1 imp truth - Engineers are the world's biggest JUGAADUS. Which also makes us great hires!

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
YouTube-ing or social media is a super new age career. It requires a complete new kind of skill set.

At the top of that skill set is INSTINCT. Take decisions only when you feel 100% certain about that decision.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Of course, MCNs exist even today. The ones that are doing well are the few which are ETHICAL. That's what a young influencer should look out for - human values and ethics.

Most 'evil' MCNs treated talents like assets or non-living property, instead of treating them like HUMANS!

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
The one thing I learnt from Engg college was NEVER TO GO WITH THE HERD. 

Most YouTubers were signing up with MCNs. All of them eventually backed out of the agreements after long, gruesome court battles.

Proved to me yet again - Trust your instinct, not the herd.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
An MCN's business model is simple - They provide production help, editing help, scripting help and above all MONETARY HELP (all of which unfortunately would always be below par)

In return, the mcn would partly own your channel. So any money you make, gets divided

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
2015 was all about India latching on to the YouTube game. There weren't too many channels back then and it was the right time to start (if you wanted to make it big!)

Enter : MCNs or multi channel networks.

I started back in 2015 and things were very different back then. Things have changed now but some golden rules are still the same. Read on...

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
The age of social media influencers promoting mental health issues as "cool" and "relatable" is passing.

If they're issues, then address them - that is correct!

But if they're issues, then SOLVE them - that is even more correct.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Instead of medicating yourself for mental health issues, try this :-

Quit drinking, smoking and other addictions.

Reduce your intake of processed food, sugar and red meat.

Cut negative people off from your life.

Meditate for 20 mins everyday for a month.

Join a gym.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
It's not your fault that you're dealing with mental health issues, it is the fault of the society that we live in.

Alcohol, sugar, drugs, excess meat are all normalised today

Dark thoughts grow out of dark habits. Step 1 to battling these issues :-

Clean up your lifestyle üèãÔ∏è

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Practicing yoga, cleaning up my lifestyle, quitting alcohol taught me 1 BIG lesson - Your mental state depends entirely on what you put your body through.

That's also the answer to ALL the mental health issues we're seeing lately. Ofcourse they're real, but so are their causes.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia

text:

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Quitting alcohol was one of the best things I ever did. Once you quit, you realise things!

The alcohol cycle :-
1. Look forward to drinking because of daily worries
2. Drink
3. Forget worries for a bit. Have fun.
4. Wake up, forget about the fun you had, start worrying again.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Mentality at 21 - "He doesn't need alcohol to have fun? What a boring guy. What a boring life! That's some infectious level of BORING."

Mentality at 25 - "He doesn't need alcohol to have fun? Wow. What a lucky guy! That's some infectious level of self-satisfaction!"

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
3 biggest life lessons from @akshaykumar 

1. Be proud of your strengths, but constantly work on your weaknesses.

2. Fitness and discipline in lifewill be your anchor, even in the most stormy seas.

3. Reinvention at all points - stay FRESH forever, stay RELEVANT forever.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Something I learnt from Akshay Kumar - Always work hard, but also always work hard to reinvent yourself. 

There will be mistakes and setbacks, but if you keep at it, people will grow to LOVE the new version of you.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
In business, but ESPECIALLY in the content business - REINVENTION is the game. Your product (videos) should add value, but at all points - the product designer (YouTuber) MUST leave room for reinvention.

Keep your core values constant. But keep adding a new "VIBE" every 6 months

text:
2 big mistakes that young bros make :-

1. The ones who are chasing success - Chase more, LEAP LESS. 
Think more, take fewer BIG, BALLSY actions.

text:
From the point of view of creators - I feel anyone selling negativity as content is doing it for easy views.

I know how much i sound like a figurative "church girl" or a figurative Captain America. But seriously - why can't we all just make positive content that adds value?

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text:
Angry, Negative video content will affect your YOUNG viewers very negatively. Remember that they look up to you! You may be fighting your personal battles but remember - you're sending out THIS message :

"Fighting is good, abuse is good - this is how to be a real man"

Very sad.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text: A big social media following is POWER. And with great power comes great responsibility. This kind of negative video content is an abuse of that power. You're spreading hate, you're spreading anger. Instead of being the Spiderman that you set out to be, you're becoming Osbourne :(

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text: Damn son. Just so much negativity on YouTube lately. Fights, disses, expose videos! Creators need to remember this - what you put out into the world (or on the internet) will return to you. In equal amounts in the real world and 1000x on the internet.

The one common theme in all books/articles on Spirituality :- 
Life is a MIX of 2 kinds of quests. 
The first is your householder journey : work, family, money.
The 2nd is your spiritual journey : karma, meditation, knowledge, charity.
It's important to advance in both!

text: Especially in romantic relationships. Don't look towards common points of interest as THE ONLY formula for compatibility. Look towards the peace, the positivity and the ENERGY LEVEL.

name: Ranveer Allahbadia
text: This is the golden rule of compatibility. Not just in romantic relationships but relationships of every kind - friendship, business, love. If your energy level is HIGHER after meeting a certain person, that's how you know whether they should be in your life or not!
